> Our 20-minute twist on this classic Thai broth is the perfect thing for busy evenings. Delicate white fish, fresh herbs, red Thai curry paste, lime and fresh vegetables are gently combined in a warming noodle soup before being topped with cashews and chopped coriander for a layer of delicious texture. Fresh, zesty, light and comforting, our Tom Yum soup is a guaranteed dinner winner.

== Prep ==

Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}.

Trim the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and sliced thinly).

Trim and coarsely grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and coarsely grated) (no need to peel).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

== Soup ==

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #large saucepan{} over medium-high heat.

When hot, add the mushrooms and fry until turning golden, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring
occasionally. Add more oil if you need to!

Stir in the @red Thai style paste{1%tbsp} and the carrot. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @coconut milk{400%ml}(light), @water{300%ml}, @vegetable stock powder{1/2%tsp}
and @sugar{1/4%tsp} into the #saucepan{}. Bring to the boil then reduce to a simmer.

Pop in the @egg noodle nests{2}, stir, and simmer for ~{3%minutes}.

== Cook the Fish ==

Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1}(cut into 4 wedges) into 4 wedges.

Chop the @cod fillets{2} into bite-sized pieces.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish!

Add the cod pieces to the saucepan and stir in gently.

Simmer for ~{3-5%minutes} until the fish is cooked through.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle!

== To Serve ==

Divide the soup between your #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkling of the
@cashew pieces{25%g}, the spring onion and the rest of the coriander.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Serve the remaining lime wedges at the side. Enjoy!